         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden ¶ 29/3/73 ¶ The Chief Inspector of Stock ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ In reply to your communication just received ¶  I have the honor to inform you, that the herb, which produced poisonous effect...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">73.03.29</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Kerr</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">D73/4020, unit 663, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For a published version of this letter see B73.07.02.</p>
               </note>Melbourne bot. Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">29/3/73</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Chief Inspector of Stock</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reply to your communication just received<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>See J. Kerr to M, 28 March 1873 (in this edition as 73-03-28b).</p>
               </note> I have the honor to inform you, that the herb, which produced poisonous effect on the cattle of Broadmeadows<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.</p>
               </note> is the <name key="Solanum%20nigrum">Solanum nigrum</name>, called in Britain the annual Nightshade.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marginal annotation in an unknown hand: 'Take in plate'. The printed version includes a plate of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Solanum%20nigrum">Solanum nigrum</name>:</seg> 73-03-29_image01.jpg </p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
               </note> It is a cosmopolitan plant, since ancient times known as poisonous and mentioned under the name of <name key="Strychnos">Strychnos</name> along with <name key="Atropa%20Belladonna">Atropa Belladonna</name> in the writings of Dioskorides already, it belonging indeed with the Belladonna and <name key="Mandragora">Mandragora</name>, <name key="Stramonium">Stramonium</name> to the same order of plants (<name key="Solaneae">Solaneae</name>).<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There is a summary of the views of Dioskorides in </seg>Dodoens (1574); a <seg style="">copy of this that M owned is now in the library of the Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> The most active principle of <name key="Solanum%20nigrum">Solanum nigrum</name> is a Glucosid, Solanin, and this is most strongly developed in the unripe berries. The plant however acts not with the dreadful intensity of the deadly Nightshade (<name key="Atropa%20Belladonna">Atropa Belladonna</name>); but it is far more commonly dispersed, and disseiminates itself with celerity, particularly on roadsides, waste places, in gardens &amp;c. It being however an annual, it can be readily enough destroyed by weeding prior to its ripening its berries. The Solanin produces paralysis of the extremities prior to death, when consumed in quantity.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's report was one of several on the poisoning that Kerr in due course forwarded to the Chief Secretary, James Francis; see </seg>D73/4020, unit 663, VPRS 3991 inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be your obedient</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Direct. botan. Garden.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
